Croatian Government May Talk to Prosecutor on Mol, HINA Reports

-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 
2011-06-28T15:23:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/croatian-government-may-talk-to-prosecutor-on-mol-hina-reports.html
Croatian Premier  Jadranka Kosor  said
a government representative will meet with the Prosecutor
General to discuss media allegations related to Hungary’s
refiner Mol Nyrt.,  HINA  reported.  Kosor said the meeting should be organized to see what the
government can do to protect national interests, according to
the  news agency .  Mol Nyrt., Hungary’s largest refiner that controls INA
Industrije Nafte d.d., on June 21 rejected allegations published
in the Croatian press that its Chairman Zsolt Hernadi bribed
Croatian Ex-Premier Ivo Sanader to help gain control over the
Croatian refiner.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jasmina Kuzmanovic in Zagreb at 
 jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  